       <article calculateheight="true" class="entry-wrapper no-border">
        <h2 class="articletitle">
         Six companies short-listed for long-term power purchase plan
        </h2>
        <div class="info-container">
         <span class="author">
          <span id="ctl00_ArticleDetails_TMI_lblAuthor">
           Malta Independent
          </span>
         </span>
         <span class="date-published">
          Saturday, 10 August 2013, 13:34
         </span>
         <span class="last-update">
          Last update: about 2 years ago
         </span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-container">
         <span class="rectangle-ad-container article-ad">
          <iframe allowtransparency="true" class="tmiads" data-src="http://ads.independent.com.mt/www/delivery/afr.php?resize=1&amp;zoneid=22&amp;target=_blank&amp;cb=4" frameborder="0" height="250" id="ad1ea670" name="ad1ea670" scrolling="no" width="300">
           <a href="http://ads.independent.com.mt/www/delivery/ck.php?n=afef72b0&amp;cb=4" target="_blank">
            <img alt="" border="0" data-src="http://ads.independent.com.mt/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=22&amp;cb=4&amp;n=afef72b0"/>
           </a>
          </iframe>
         </span>
         <p>
          Enemalta Corporation has announced that six consortia have been short-listed for the long-term power purchase and gas supply agreement.
         </p>
         <p>
          They are:
         </p>
         <p>
          Daewoo Shipping and Marine Engineering Company Ltd
         </p>
         <p>
          ElectroGas Malta Consortium
         </p>
         <p>
          Edison SPA
         </p>
         <p>
          Endeavour Energy Holdings LLC and Exodus Crossing LLC
         </p>
         <p>
          Soffimat Gestamp
         </p>
         <p>
          Yildirim Tecnicas Power and Gas
         </p>
         <p>
          The corporation said that the shortlisting was possible because the companies satisfied the criteria established, which will lead to the reduction of energy tariffs and cleaner environment as promised by the Labour Party.
         </p>
         <p>
          The Energy Ministry said that this government started to work on its energy plan from day one after taking office, issuing a call for expressions of interest within one month following the election.
         </p>
         <p>
          Originally there were 19 submissions, which showed the level of interest generated by the project. These have now been brought down to six, an indication that the project is on track.
         </p>
         <p>
          Apart from this process, studies are being carried out so that Mepa will eventually issue the necessary permits after a period of consultation with all those concerned, the government said.
         </p>
         <div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style">
          <a class="addthis_button_facebook_like" fb:like:layout="button_count">
          </a>
          <a class="addthis_button_tweet">
          </a>
          <a class="addthis_button_google_plusone" g:plusone:size="medium">
          </a>
          <a class="addthis_counter addthis_pill_style">
